column2: ltpug_eng
Land total
為顧及數據的精確度及保障個別受訪者的私隱，人數少的小規劃統計區會與鄰近的小規劃統計區合併為「小規劃統計區－小合併組」或「小規劃統計區－大合併組」後才發布統計數字。「小規劃統計區－小合併組」及「小規劃統計區－大合併組」的人口分別為最少1 000人及最少10 000人。
(1) - 數字包括報稱有多於一個種族的人士。
(2) - 數字不包括失去語言能力的人士。
(3) - 同區就讀的人士包括（a）在香港島或九龍居住並在同一區議會分區內上課的人士，（b）在新市鎮居住並在同一新市鎮上課的人士，及（c）在新界其他地方居住並在同一區議會分區非新市鎮地區內上課的人士。
(4) - 勞動人口佔所有 15 歲及以上人口的百分比。
(5) - 2021年人口普查所採用非從事經濟活動人口的經濟活動身分分類（即「料理家務者」、「學生」、「退休人士」、「無酬照顧者」及「其他」），跟2011年人口普查及2016年中期人口統計所採用的分類（即「料理家務者」、「學生」、「退休人士」及「其他」）稍有分別，因此2021年統計數字與2011年及／或2016年統計數字作比較時須加以留意。
(6) - 無酬照顧者指須無酬照顧親人或其他人士（包括長期病患、殘疾或年長／年幼的人士）的人。
(7) - 同區工作的人士包括（a）在香港島或九龍居住並在同一區議會分區內工作的人士，（b）在新市鎮居住並在同一新市鎮工作的人士，及（c）在新界其他地方居住並在同一區議會分區非新市鎮地區內工作的人士。於家中工作的人士並不包括在內。
(8) - 2021 年人口普查採用了新的職業分類方法，此職業分類方法更為貼近「國際標準職業分類法2008 年版」。
(9) - 數字是按「香港標準行業分類2.0 版」為藍本的行業分類而編製。
(10) - 「其他」包括「農業、林業及漁業」、「採礦及採石」、「電力及燃氣供應」、「自來水供應；污水處理、廢棄物管理及污染防治活動」等行業，及報稱的行業不能辨別或描述不足。
(11) - 由一對已婚夫婦而並無其他親屬所組成的住戶。這類住戶可包括或不包括其他無親屬關係的同住人士，例如家庭傭工。
(12) - 由一對夫婦及其未婚子女而並無其他親屬所組成的住戶。這類住戶可包括或不包括其他無親屬關係的同住人士，例如家庭傭工。
(13) - 由父／母一方及其未婚子女而並無其他親屬所組成的住戶。這類住戶可包括或不包括其他無親屬關係的同住人士，例如家庭傭工。
(14) - 由一對夫婦及其至少一個父或母親（包括夫婦雙方的父母親）而並無其他親屬所組成的住戶。這類住戶可包括或不包括其他無親屬關係的同住人士，例如家庭傭工。
(15) - 由一對夫婦、至少一個父或母親（包括夫婦雙方的父母親）及其未婚子女而並無其他親屬所組成的住戶。這類住戶可包括或不包括其他無親屬關係的同住人士，例如家庭傭工。
(16) - 由一羣有親屬關係人士所組成但未能歸入其他類別的住戶。這類住戶可包括或不包括其他無親屬關係的同住人士，例如家庭傭工。
(17) -只有一個人的住戶。
(18) - 由一羣無親屬關係人士所組成的住戶。
(19) - 從事經濟活動的家庭住戶是指家庭住戶內除外籍家庭傭工外至少有一名其他成員從事經濟活動。
(20) - 租金金額是 0 的住戶包括居住在親友家中無論是否得到許可而沒有繳付租金的住戶、向三房客收取的租金總值超過或相等於大租的二房東住戶及由僱主免費提供住所的住戶。
(21) - 數字不包括居於非屋宇單位或船艇的家庭住戶。與其他住戶共同佔用的樓面面積不包括在內。
(22) - 曾作內部遷移的人士指該人士的現住地區與其5年前的居住地區不同。在分析內部遷移時，居住地區的轉變是指（a）一區議會分區與另一區議會分區之間的遷移，或（b）在新界同一區議會分區內，一新市鎮與另一新市鎮之間的遷移，或一新市鎮與該區其他地方之間的遷移。
(23) - 數字包括現住於 5 年前住址，但在 5 年期間曾遷往其他地方，並稍後遷回的人士。

Having regard to data precision and protection of data privacy of individual respondents, a Tertiary Planning Unit (TPU) with a small population is merged with adjacent TPU(s) as a Small TPU Group or Large TPU Group for the release of statistics.  There are at least 1 000 persons and at least 10 000 persons in a Small TPU Group and a Large TPU Group respectively.
(1) - Figures include persons who reported more than one ethnicity.
(2) - Figures exclude mute persons.

(3) - Persons who study in the same district include: (a) those who live on Hong Kong Island or in Kowloon and study in the same District Council district; (b) those who live in a new town and study in the same new town; and (c) those who live in other areas in the New Territories and study in areas other than new town areas of the same District Council district.
(4) - The proportion of labour force in the total population aged 15 and over.

(5) - The classification of economic activity status for economically inactive population adopted in the 2021 Population Census (i.e. “Home-makers”, “Students”, “Retired persons”, “Unpaid carers” and “Others”) slightly differs from that adopted in the 2011 Population Census and 2016 Population By-census (i.e. “Home-makers”, “Students”, “Retired persons” and “Others”). Therefore, caution should be taken when comparing figures for 2021 with those for 2011 and/or 2016.
(6) - Unpaid carers refer to persons who are engaged in unpaid care to family members or other persons (including persons with chronic diseases/disability and old/young persons).

(7) - Persons who work in the same district include: (a) those who live on Hong Kong Island or in Kowloon and work in the same District Council district; (b) those who live in a new town and work in the same new town; and (c) those who live in other areas in the New Territories and work in areas other than new town areas of the same District Council district. Persons who work at home are excluded.
(8) - A new occupation classification scheme which follows “International Standard Classification Occupations 2008 (ISCO-08)” more closely was adopted in the 2021 Population Census.
(9) - Figures are compiled based on the industry classification modelled on the Hong Kong Standard Industrial Classification Version 2.0.

(10) - "Others" include "Agriculture, forestry and fishing"; "Mining and quarrying"; "Electricity and gas supply"; "Water supply; sewerage, waste management and remediation activities" and industrial activities unidentifiable or inadequately described.
(11) - A household comprising a married couple without any other related persons. It may or may not include other unrelated persons (e.g. domestic helpers).
(12) - A household comprising a couple and their unmarried child(ren) without any other related persons. It may or may not include other unrelated persons (e.g. domestic helpers).
(13) - A household comprising a father or mother and his/ her unmarried child(ren) without any other related persons. It may or may not include other unrelated persons (e.g. domestic helpers).

(14) - A household comprising a couple and at least one of their parents (including the parent(s) of the wife and/ or husband) without any other related persons. It may or may not include other unrelated persons (e.g. domestic helpers).

(15) - A household comprising a couple, at least one of their parents (including the parent(s) of the wife and/ or husband) and their unmarried children without any other related persons. It may or may not include other unrelated persons (e.g. domestic helpers).
(16) - A household comprising a group of related persons but not being classified in the other categories. It may or may not include other unrelated persons (e.g. domestic helpers).
(17) - A household with only one person.
(18) - A household comprising unrelated person(s).
(19) - Economically active household refers to a domestic household with at least one member (excluding foreign domestic helpers) being economically active.

(20) - Zero rent households include households living in accommodation of friends or relatives without paying any rent with or without permission, main tenant households with total rental receipts from sub-tenant(s) greater than or equal to rent paid, and those households whose quarters were provided free by employers.
(21) - Figures exclude domestic households living in unsheltered accommodation or on board vessels. Floor area of common area shared among households is excluded.

(22) - Persons having internally migrated were those whose area of current residence was different from the area of residence 5 years ago. In defining internal migration, a change in the area of residence refers to a move (a) from a District Council district to another District Council district; or (b) within a District Council district in the New Territories, from a new town to another new town, or from a new town to other areas in the district or vice versa.
(23) - Figures include persons who currently live in the same address as 5 years ago but had moved elsewhere during the 5 years and then moved back.
